aboutSections.name: About
aboutSections.description: Roasted and peeled poblano chile stuffed in cheese, dipped into a souffl batter then deep fried perfection and served on top a tomatoey salsa rancha. Works fantastic with anaheim chiles or even large and long jalapeos!

steps.description: Completely char the peppers then allow them to steam for ten minutes. Then peel them and remove the seeds, stuff them with grated cheese and the epazote or cilantro and thread with a toothpick to seal them.
Make the souffl batter by whipping the egg whites into stiff peaks then incorporate the yolks and salt.
Broil all the vegetables then add to a blender with oregano and salt and simmer for ten minutes.
Add a generous amount of salsa to each plate, add a chile, and serve with any sides you like. Enjoy!
